-- NSW Plans to Sell State's Waste Management Assets, Financial Review Says
-- Nichola Saminather
-- 2010-07-23T22:43:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-23/nsw-plans-to-sell-state-s-waste-management-assets-financial-review-says.html

          
          
             New South Wales has received
interest from private equity bidders and trade buyers for its
waste management arm, WSN, which may sell for more than A$200
million, the Australian Financial Review reported in its Street
Talk column. Private equity firms including Ironbridge and
Archer Capital, and trade buyers including Transpacific
Industries, Sita Australia, Thiess and Veolia Environmental
Services may have expressed interested, according to the report.  
